post_text:
The Two Rock team is so grateful for all of the support we receive from volunteers! Thank you for all the ways you make our school stronger. From driving on field trips, reading with students, making tamales, teaching students new skills, helping in our garden, to helping with special projects, our volunteers are an invaluable part of our Two Rock team. We didn't get to celebrate you in person this year, but we still celebrate you! Thank you!

El equipo de Two Rock está muy agradecido por todo el apoyo que recibimos de los voluntarios. Gracias por todas las formas en que hacen más fuerte a nuestra escuela. Desde conducir en excursiones, leer con los estudiantes, hacer tamales, enseñar a los estudiantes nuevas habilidades, ayudar en nuestro jardín, hasta ayudar en proyectos especiales, nuestros voluntarios son una parte invaluable de nuestro equipo de Two Rock. No pudimos celebrarte en persona este año, ¡pero aún así te celebramos! ¡Gracias!

No pudimos celebrarte en persona este año, ¡pero aún así te celebramos! ¡Gracias!

post_text:
Our Two Rock Staff Car Parade is tomorrow (Wednesday)! We will leave campus at about 2:30, go up to the Coast Guard base and most likely drive the route of the Christmas parade. After we leave the base, we will drive by some of our local ranches. We look forward to waving to you!

¡Nuestro desfile de autos de Two Rock Staff es mañana (miércoles)! Saldremos del campus aproximadamente a las 2:30, subiremos a la base de la Guardia Costera y probablemente conduzcamos la ruta del desfile de Navidad. Después de salir de la base, pasaremos por algunos de nuestros ranchos locales. ¡Esperamos saludarte!

post_text: A little piece of local and Coast Guard history for a California history lesson and #MilitaryMonday
shared_text:
Point Reyes National Seashore Association
April 20 at 6:02 PM ·

For #MilitaryMonday we want to highlight one of our oldest facilities, the Historic Lifeboat Station! Reconstructed in 1911 the facility use to reside on Great beach, now renamed and split into North and South Beach. After a few years of launching straight into the Pacific Ocean and having misfortune, the Coast Guard moved it into Drakes Bay which improved all essential functions for the Coast Guard. It has since stayed there and now serves as an educational overnight facility for us!
-
-
#ParkInPlace #PointReyes_PRNSA #PointReyesNPS #FindYourPark #EncuentraTuParque #NationalParkWeek

Student work packets are ready to pick up, and you can also turn completed work in. Each student has their own folder organized by class, so work is easy to find. Please note that Thursday is the last day work will be available for pick up this week. We will also be changing our pick-up protocols to maintain social distance among families during work pick-up.

Los paquetes de trabajo de los estudiantes están listos para recoger, y también puedes entregar el trabajo terminado. Cada estudiante tiene su propia carpeta organizada por clase, así que el trabajo es fácil de encontrar. Tengan en cuenta que el jueves es el último día en que el trabajo estará disponible para ser recogido esta semana. También cambiaremos los protocolos de recogida para mantener la distancia social entre las familias durante la recogida del trabajo.

Two Rock Elementary School
Dear Two Rock Families,

First, we want you to know that we miss you and your amazing students and we hope you are all well. Second, we want you to know that we are working intensively to create remote learning resources for our students and will have packets ready for pick up on Monday after 10 am. You will receive more details soon, and teachers will also send details that are specific to their classes. Thanks for your patience and please take good care!

Estimadas familias de Two Rock,

Primero, queremos que sepan que los extrañamos a ustedes y a sus increíbles estudiantes y esperamos que estén bien. Segundo, queremos que sepa que estamos trabajando intensamente para crear recursos de aprendizaje a distancia para nuestros estudiantes y tendremos los paquetes listos para ser recogidos el lunes después de las 10 de la mañana. Pronto recibirán más detalles, y los profesores también enviarán detalles específicos para sus clases. Gracias por su paciencia y por favor cuídense!

Dear Two Rock Families,

We want to update you regarding school closure or suspension of in-person instruction. Some Sonoma County schools have announced closures already. While we don't have an answer yet, there is a meeting with county health officials and superintendents on Monday. We should be able to communicate our plans to you on Monday afternoon. Thank you for your patience.

Estimadas familias de Two Rock: Queremos informarles sobre el cierre de la escuela o la suspensión de la instrucción en persona. Algunas escuelas del condado de Sonoma ya han anunciado cierres. Si bien aún no tenemos una respuesta, hay una reunión con los funcionarios de salud del condado y los superintendentes el lunes. Deberíamos poder comunicarle nuestros planes el lunes por la tarde. Gracias por su paciencia.

We haven't posted much lately because we have been too busy! Next week, we will hold our winter concert on Thursday 12/19 at 10:15 am and we will follow up with a family crafting activity. We hope you will join us! Fall Report Cards will also go home that day.

We will close all school functions, including aftercare and the school office, at 1:00 on December 19 so that staff may attend a community event together. Please make plans accordingly.

We haven't posted much lately because we have been too busy! Next week, we will hold our winter concert on Thursday 12/19 at 10:15 am and we will follow up with a family crafting activity. We hope you will join us! Fall Report Cards will also go home that day.

We will close all school functions, including aftercare and the school office, at 1:00 on December 19 so that staff may attend a community event together. Please make plans accordingly.

We hope to see you all at the winter concert that morning!

Two Rock Elementary will be closed on Wednesday, 10/30, as we prepare school for students to return and assess other conditions that may impact our reopening, including weather, fire, and air conditions. We will update the community on our plans for Thursday around mid-day on Wednesday. Again, thank you for your patience!

Two Rock Elementary estará cerrada el miércoles 10/30, mientras preparamos la escuela para que los estudiantes regresen y evalúen otras condiciones que pueden afectar nuestra reapertura, incluyendo el clima, el fuego y las condiciones del aire. Actualizaremos a la comunidad en nuestros planes para el jueves alrededor del mediodía del miércoles. ¡De nuevo, gracias por su paciencia!

A Unity Day rainbow at Two Rock!

Unity Day is an international antibullying campaign, and we are showing our community strength and commitment to stand up to bullying. The rainbow is a symbol for the whole community being stronger than the sum of our parts. Each class is a community, but we are even stronger together, and we support each other.

Dear Two Rock Community,

We want to let you know that our fabulous District Secretary, Michelle Panizzera, will be making a transition out of our school office in the next few weeks. She has a great opportunity to grow and develop as a business manager in a nearby district. We have already posted the position and are currently looking for candidates. Michelle will be supporting our school through this transition, so you will still see her on campus for awhile. We are so excited for her but sad for us!

Tiene una gran oportunidad de crecer y desarrollarse como gerente de negocios en un distrito cercano. Ya hemos publicado el puesto y estamos buscando candidatos. Michelle apoyará a nuestra escuela durante esta transición, así que todavía la verán en el campus por un tiempo. Estamos tan emocionados por ella pero tristes por nosotros!

post_text: The National Weather Service is reporting strong wind events and have issued a Fire Weather Watch for Wednesday, October 9, at 5:00 am through Thursday, October 10, at 5:00 pm. PG&E has discussed the possibility of a Public Safety Power Shutoff (PSPS) and we are awaiting an announcement from them. We are preparing for a possible PSPS on Wednesday and Thursday. Our goal is to keep school open if we can do so safely. We will disseminate information to you as we receive it. Thank you for your patience and support!
text: The National Weather Service is reporting strong wind events and have issued a Fire Weather Watch for Wednesday, October 9, at 5:00 am through Thursday, October 10, at 5:00 pm. PG&E has discussed the possibility of a Public Safety Power Shutoff (PSPS) and we are awaiting an announcement from them. We are preparing for a possible PSPS on Wednesday and Thursday. Our goal is to keep school open if we can do so safely. We will disseminate information to you as we receive it. Thank you for your patience and support!

post_text: We had a fantastic day today! Our Cardboard Challenge was amazing, and the student-created arcade games were brilliant, resourceful, and well-crafted. Everyone had tons of fun while learning how to build and engineer, collaborate with others, think critically to solve problems, and improvise solutions. We can’t wait for our Boat Race Challenge in November!

We will have another Coffee with the Superintendent-Principal on the base this Thursday at 9 am. Coffee with the Principal is an opportunity to talk informally about anything related to school, and to ask questions directly. It is a great way for us to learn about our school community and take care of concerns that we might not otherwise know about.

This is our monthly routine - first Thursday of the month - so if we don't see you this week, we hope to see you in the future!
